Leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Nnamdi Kanu, has been arrested. Credible sources in the office of the Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice told LEADERSHIP that Kanu has been extradited to Nigeria to face trial at the Federal High Court in Abuja on Tuesday. Kanu is facing charges bordering on treasonable felony instituted against him at the federal high court in Abuja in response to years of campaign for the independent Republic of Biafra through IPOB.  He was granted bail in April 2017 for health reasons but skipped bail after flouting some of the conditions given to him by the court. He has also been on the run since then after soldiers raided his father’s residence in Abia state. Details Later…